import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['record'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Record Temperatures')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of record temperatures?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual Temperature')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['normal'], label='Normal Temperature')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How do actual temperatures compare to normal temperatures?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    
    average_forecast = data['forecast'].mean()
    
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='day', y='forecast', legend=False)
    ax.axhline(y=average_forecast, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Forecast: {average_forecast:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average forecasted temperature for the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
